<title type="html"><![CDATA[Using TASes for emulator testing]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8511&amp;p=88717#p88717"><![CDATA[
In my emulator I got all SMB movies to sync without problems (with add/remove idle frames in the beginning).  I update the controller data at the beginning of vertical blanking (scanline 241). With all NES movies, the controller data is updated regardless of whether the game polls the input 1, 2 or 0 times; and regardless of whether NMI is to be triggered or not.<br />Make sure you properly distinguish input for different controllers.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5043">Bisqwit</a> — Tue Jan 10, 2012 12:50 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
